features: DUAL USE: The Ashton is a functional changing table that is a nursery must-have! Built of durable, sustainable, and reclaimed New Zealand pinewood, you can use it as a changing station in the early years and then as a nightstand as your child grows older.

FUNCTIONAL & SECURE: Don’t worry about a mess during changing time as it comes with a water-resistant mattress pad. With safety rails on four sides the changing table is a fully enclosed & secure space; there’s also a safety strap for keeping baby secure. Also, 1 inch mattress pad is included.

GREAT STORAGE: The Ashton comes with two easy-to-reach, spacious shelves below the changing table - keep your child’s essentials neatly organized and within easy reach! Product dimensions are 34L x 20W x 40H inches.

BEAUTIFUL FINISHES: The Ashton sports a clean design and is available in vibrant eco-friendly and child-safe water-based finishes. Mix and match with Dream On Me cribs as you design a stylish and cheery nursery space for your child.
SAFETY MATTERS: The Ashton is tested for lead/other toxic elements and meets applicable CPSC/ASTM standards. All tools for assembly included. Maximum weight limit is 30 lbs.
body.description: A nursery is incomplete without a changing table and the Ashton 2-in-1 Changing Table is a functional and stylish solution that combines effortlessly with a variety of nursery themes and colour palettes. Use it as a changing station when your child is young, and as your child grows older, use it as a night stand! The mattress changing platform features a water-resistant mattress pad for mess-free changing! Safety rails surround the changing station on four sides making the table a fully enclosed and secure space. There is also a safety strap for keeping baby secure. The Ashton is tested for lead and other toxic elements and meets or exceeds CPSC and ASTM standards. It comes with two easy-to-reach, spacious shelves below the changing table - keep your LOs essentials neatly organized and easy to access! Made of durable, sustainable and renewable New Zealand pinewood, it features a clean design and is available in vibrant eco-friendly and child-safe water-based finishes. Mix and match with Dream On Me cribs as you design a beautiful and fun nursery space for your child Product dimensions are 34L x 20W x 40H inches; maximum weight limit 30 lbs. What’s more? The 2 in 1 Ashton Changing Table comes with 1 inch mattress pad. All tools for assembly included.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 24, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exactly What I Needed
reviews.reviewText: After a very frustrating experience with another amazon seller and a different changing table, I chose this one and I'm glad I did. It shipped out and was delivered a full 2 days before the estimate. Price was great. It was fairly simple to put together, husband started it while I was feeding our newborn and I finished it when little dude was done eating. (I enjoy putting together furniture weirdly enough.) Not a ton of pieces or hardware. The instructions are a tad confusing but just be patient and you can do it. Looks great in our son's nursery with his black crib.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 2, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Get this cute changing table!
reviews.reviewText: Overall, I love this changing table. It was slightly difficult to put this together and I would recommend 2 people for an easy, quick assembly. However, it’s nothing crazy. Also, make sure you tighten the two bolts on the bottom after you finish screwing everything just to make sure it’s super sturdy. I love that it has tons of room to store stuff (as you can see) and it’s super cute. The changing pad is thin but it didn’t bother me because I was creative and took another changing pad, purchased a sheet for it, and made it into a pillow cushion for baby. 🙂

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful design and great value
reviews.reviewText: Aside from some minor paint and surface imperfections, this changing table is well worth the money. If indentations that do not go deeper than the paint bother you, you may want to skip out and buy direct from a furniture store. It feels sturdy, is a great height for someone taller like me, and looks fantastic with my Kalani crib, even though they are different brands. I highly recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 23, 2017
reviews.reviewText: This is a wonderful addition to the nursery. It has lots of storage room on each shelf. The unit is quite sturdy and has a nice design and finish. I was surprised to see that the shelves are a very light lavender on the withe finish unit, and it also came with a changing pad which I was not aware of. Very easy to assemble.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2018
reviews.reviewText: I was hesitant to buy this due to the mixed reviews and tales of damaged items but, the price was right after spending on all of those essential baby items getting ready for little one's arrival. I was able to put it together in less than an hour, by myself at 9 months pregnant. As others have stated, the changing pad is rather thin. I bought the "Summer Infant Changing Pad" as a supplement but in order to attach it, you have to make an extra hole and I just was not willing to do that. The top of the table has two, pre-drilled holes to secure the changing straps for the pad that is included, so I plan on just sticking with the thin pad and hoping my baby doesn't mind. There were a few defects in the wood upon arrival, not scratches really because the color did not come off but little indentations in the wood on the railing from the pieces coming together during shipping (shown in 2nd photo). They are not even noticeable unless you look closely and are looking for defects. The shelves seemed kind of thin at first but after putting it together I am satisfied with the strength. The whole thing seems very stable and I was able to fit 2 half size fabric storage baskets total on each shelf to keep diapers, wipes and other supplies handy. I think that this was a good buy and I am satisfied, especially for the price.

reviews.reviewText: Easy assembly. Fast delivery. This change table is quite sturdy and looks great. The storage shelves are just the right height for storing our little one's essentials.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 29, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not the best quality
reviews.reviewText: This changing table was nice looking and matched the crib I purchased. I was able to receive it quickly, even though it came a day later than it should have. The reason for 3 stars is there were orange spots on the front side of the back "sleigh" that looked like rust. Very easy to see, but they faded after bleaching for a couple minutes. There was also a scuff on the front side of the front "sleigh", but not as noticeable. There were other paint imperfections here and there. It is also pictured with a contoured pad and a thin pad. Mine came with the thin pad. I would have returned it, but I needed it right away for my visiting grandchild, which was the whole reason for ordering from Amazon in the 1st place.
